  "title": "Storekeeper (Electronics Manufacturing / 5Days)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Working hours: Monday – Friday 8:30pm – 6:00pm</li><li>Birthday Leave</li><li>Work-Life Balance</li><li>Friendly and Collaborative work environment</li></ul><p><br />Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Perform day-to-day operations including receiving, checking, sorting, picking, labelling and packing of goods</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date stock records in the inventory system</li><li>Maintain housekeeping and safety in the store and warehouse</li><li>Perform cycle counts and year-end stock take</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned by Superior</li></ul><p><br />Requirements:</p><ul><li>Minimum GCE ‘N’ level  </li><li>At least 1 year of relevant work experience in electronics manufacturing environment</li><li>Able to operate Microsoft Excel and inventory/ERP System</li><li>Able to lift and carry items up to 20 kg</li><li>Able to work independently and as part of a team</li></ul>",
